anyone have a great guacamole recipe i don't like it spicy and i don't like a lot of things in it just smooth and creamy they make it like this at a local restaurant and it's delicious but i don't know how to make it myself thanks i hope you like this one creamy guacamole teaspoon grated lemon peel tablespoons lemon juice medium size soft ripe avocado cup low fat percent cottage cheese to cloves peeled garlic teaspoon salt tablespoons minced fresh cilantro fresh jalapeno or serrano chili seeded and minced see cook's note tablespoon thinly sliced green onion small tomatoes finely chopped and drained well divided use cilantro sprigs place lemon peel and lemon juice in a blender or food processor peel avocado and remove seed add avocado to blender along with cottage cheese garlic and salt whirl until smoothly pureed spoon guacamole into a serving bowl and gently stir in minced cilantro chili onion and half the tomatoes at this point you may cover and refrigerate for up to hours stir before serving to serve garnish with remaining tomatoes and cilantro sprigs Peruvian cuisine Cuisine of the Philippines Hamburger Tofu French fries Cuisine of Brazil Avocado Breakfast Hot dog Cheese Curry Cantonese cuisine Salad German cuisine Haggis Cuisine of Denmark Gazpacho Muesli Barbecue Jewish cuisine Bengali cuisine Coriander Chicken soup Recipe Salsa (sauce) Onion Vinegar Korean cuisine Ceviche Garlic Cuisine of Greece Ice cream Russian cuisine Pizza Risotto Cuisine of Africa Bread Martini cocktail Chowder Rice pudding Ramen Fish and chips Rum Hummus Cajun cuisine Tomato Soy milk Cuisine of Vietnam Kebab Laksa Mai Tai D__ner kebab Chutney Cuisine of Argentina Kraft Dinner Paneer Bagel Satay Cuisine of Malaysia McDonald's Cooking weights and measures Polish cuisine Tea French cuisine Potato salad Cuisine of Cambodia Pickling Menudo (soup) Yoghurt Cuisine of the Southern United States Soul food MRE Cooking Potato pancakes Cuisine of Thailand Porridge Dim sum Pancake Lemon Orange (fru